<p>August 7, August 14, August 21, and August 28 from 10:30 am to noon<br>
Ages 8 to 11<br>
Cost: $7.56 per child<br>
<a href="https://anc.ca.apm.activecommunities.com/ottawa/activity/search?locale=en-US&amp;activity_select_param=2&amp;center_ids=303&amp;activity_keyword=Can%20You%20Dig%20It&amp;viewMode=list">Advance registration is required.</a> Registration opens May 15 at 9 pm.</p>
<p>Learn to dig for artefacts, identify mysterious objects and use techniques that scientists use every day. Kids will get their hands dirty like Indiana Jones in a simulated excavation site at one of Ottawa's historic homes.</p>
<h4>Themes</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Archeology (August 7)</strong><br>
