            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Work with us to shape your experience. Contact the museum before your visit to discuss your needs. Information about accessibility at the facility, programs, and services is available upon request.</p>
<p>The accessibility features of this facility are detailed below. While the City of Ottawa is constantly working to improve access, please note that not all parts of every facility are necessarily 'accessible for all' as facilities were built to meet accessibility standards of their time.</p>
<p><strong>Parking</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>25 metres from parking space to the door</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Passenger Loading Zone</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Cut curb</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Entrance/Exit</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>1 &nbsp;accessible entrance</li>
<li>Ramp</li>
<li>Wide door for wheelchair passage</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Reception desks</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Floor area for manoeuvring a wheelchair</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Washrooms</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Accessible washroom on 1st floor</li>
<li>Lowered sink counters</li>
<li>Lowered towel dispensers</li>
<li>Large stalls to allow transfers</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Stairs</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Stairs with no-slip surface</li>
<li>Continuous hand rails</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Learn more about&nbsp;<a href="/en/recreation-and-parks/inclusive-recreation">Inclusive Recreation</a>&nbsp;and accessible services.</em></p>
